    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FERRY FOOD SERVICE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Robert Strauss</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Strauss, Robert</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cape May-Lewes Ferry stops serving prepared food on its five ships that run between Delaware and New Jersey after US Food and Drug Administration threatens court action when inspections uncover health violations (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Cape May-Lewes Ferry stopped serving prepared food on its five ships this week after the United States Food and Drug Administration threatened court action. The Delaware River and Bay Authority, which operates the five ferries that ply the bay between the New Jersey and Delaware resort towns, voluntarily shut down its cooked and prepared food services aboard the ferries after continued F.D.A. inspections showed violations that might threaten health of passengers. Until food service resumes, passengers can buy prepackaged food on the ferries.</p>
        <p>Robert Strauss</p>
      </block>
